merge_armature.lockmode.not_locked.body: Merged armature does not sync its position with the base avatar.
merge_armature.lockmode.base_to_merge.bo: Moving the base avatar will move the merge armature. If you move the merged armature, it will not affect the base avatar. This is useful when adding normal outfits, where you might want to adjust the position of bones in the outfit.
merge_armature.lockmode.bidirectional.bo: The base armature and the merged armature will always have the same position. This is useful when creating animations that are meant to target the base armature. In order to activate this, your armatures must already be in the exact same position.
merge_armature.reset_pos.info: This command will force the position of all bones in the outfit to match that of the base avatar. This can be helpful as a starting point for installing outfits not set up for your current avatar.
merge_armature.reset_pos.adjust_rotation: Also set rotation to base avatar
merge_armature.reset_pos.adjust_scale: Also set local scale to base avatar
merge_armature.reset_pos.heuristic_scale: Adjust outfit overall scale to match base avatar
Will set the overall scale of the outfit as a whole based on armspan measurements. Recommended for setting up outfits.

error.merge_armature.circular_dependency: Your Merge Armature component is referencing itself, or a child of itself, as the merge target.
Merge Armature should typically specify the Armature object of the avatar itself under its Target field. Don't specify the outfit itself!
error.merge_armature.physbone_on_humanoi: [MA-0002] PhysBone component found on humanoid bone

Some Humanoid bones in the armature to merge are controlled by PhysBones, and can't be merged properly because its position is different from the corresponding Humanoid bone in the merge target. You should remove the PhysBones on those Humanoid bones in the armature to merge.
